        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 9:45AM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 945 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Agate, or 20 miles northwest of Limon, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Agate.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
